      "message": "nit: I usually find it easier to debug small focused tests than big tests with a loop over test cases.\n\nFor tests with minimal setup overhead, like this one, I would do something like:\nfunc testQueriesHelper(t *testing.T, query query.Search, expected []spotCheck) {\n  unittest.SmallTest(t)\n  ...\n}\n\nfunc TestDefaultQueryReverse(t *testing.T) {\n  testQueriesHelper(t, ...)\n}\n\nFor tests with a lot of overhead, it might be useful to make testQueriesHelper an inner function and use t.Run:\nfunc TestSearchThreeDevicesQueries(t *testing.T) {\n  ...\n  helper :\u003d func(tc testCase) {\n    t.Run(tc.name, func(t *testing.T) {\n      resp, err :\u003d s.Search(context.Background(), \u0026tc.query)\n      require.NoError(t, err, tc.name)\n      ...\n    })\n  }\n  helper(testCase{\n    name: \"default query, but in reverse\",\n    ...\n  }\n}\nThis will output failures grouped by the sub-test where the failure occurred.",
